b'' b"i always believed the statement 'those who do not know their history" b'are condemned to repeat it (will durant but i am beginning to' b'believe the opposite is true.' b'' b'here in t.p.m and in other newsgroups it seems that history is' b'mainly remembered to foment hatred or to be used as a club. in the' b'history of my own people there are ample acts of shame, both done' b'by my people and done to my people. since i was not party to any' b'of those acts, i refuse to accept blame for the evil acts that my' b'ancestors committed, nor do i direct hatred toward the descendants' b'of those who committed evil acts against my ancestors.' b'' b'will all of this discussion rebuild a single mosque? will it rebuild' b'the temple? somehow i doubt that it will.' b'' b'a post in another group, on the bosnian war, asked us all to love' b'each other, that love would conquer hate. sadly, i remember a tv' b'interview with a young woman in sarajevo (sp?) who was as i remember,' b'a former olympic calibre contestant in the rifle shoot. she was now' b'trying to pick-off serbian snipers. during the communist years she' b'had married a serb, who was now fighting against her people. so it' b'seems that hate will conquer love.' b'' b'is there an odd chance that we might all forget past wrongs and try' b"and see how we might all live together? it's a damn small planet," b'which we have come very close to turning into a radioactive ball,' b'glowing softly in space. we seem to have been spared that prospect,' b"shall we now bathe it in each other's blood?" b'' b'shalom, salam, and peace' b'' b'reb' b'' 